<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="481" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1520,1907]" pageId="8" pageNumber="481">
The original description (Buresch 1919) clearly mentions a single male specimen, a 
<typeStatus box="[1131,1282,1737,1763]" pageId="8" pageNumber="481">paralectotype</typeStatus>
from the type series of 
<taxonomicName authority="Buresch, 1919" authorityName="Buresch" authorityYear="1919" box="[259,734,1773,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Satyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arethusa" subSpecies="strumata">
<emphasis box="[259,560,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="481">Satyrus arethusa strumata</emphasis>
Buresch, 1919
</taxonomicName>
(see also specimen with identifier “NMNHS-INV-T-01015”, account “ 
<emphasis box="[259,359,1810,1835]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="481">strumata</emphasis>
Buresch, 1919” below). The date is, however, 13 August, as with all the specimens of the type series of 
<emphasis box="[254,360,1846,1871]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="481">strumata,</emphasis>
and not July, “ 
<date box="[532,663,1845,1871]" pageId="8" pageNumber="481" value="1917-07-13">13. 7. 1917</date>
”, as it was stated originally. Infrasubspecific, not an available name, Article 10.2 (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission of Zoological Nomenclature" box="[299,434,1881,1907]" pageId="8" pageNumber="481" refId="ref15744" refString="ICZN [International Commission of Zoological Nomenclature] (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth edition, adopted by the International Union of Biological Sciences. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, c / o The Natural History Museum, London, xxx + 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
